00:28.115 --> 00:30.204
to anyone
you've briefly dated.

00:30.247 --> 00:31.248
As a rule,
we'd like to keep

00:31.292 --> 00:33.685
the hyper-sexualized greetings
to a minimum.

00:33.729 --> 00:35.861
If I have to follow the rule,
you should, too.

00:36.906 --> 00:39.343
Okay.
I said it one time.

00:40.736 --> 00:42.085
Hey, you.

00:43.695 --> 00:44.479
Hey, you.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.048
Hey, you.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.442
I have a life.

00:51.486 --> 00:54.184
I have needs.
Call me romantic.

00:54.228 --> 00:55.229
Nobody's calling you
romantic.No one's calling you
romantic.

00:55.272 --> 00:56.404
But when I've been
with someone,

00:56.447 --> 00:58.101
it means something to me.

00:58.145 --> 00:59.668
"Hey, you"...

00:59.711 --> 01:01.191
...is my tip of the cap

01:01.235 --> 01:03.150
to a beautiful
experience.

01:06.240 --> 01:07.545
Hey, you.

01:11.549 --> 01:14.422
What? You're the only one
with a history?

01:14.465 --> 01:17.425
--Captions by VITAC--

01:19.818 --> 01:21.298
Romance!

01:21.342 --> 01:25.259
Your next film
is going to be a romance

01:25.302 --> 01:29.263
from the 12th century tale
of "Tristan and Isol--"

01:29.306 --> 01:31.395
Forget it.

01:31.439 --> 01:33.180
I got dumped,
and I need to feel good again.

01:33.223 --> 01:35.356
Sue me. What?

01:35.399 --> 01:39.273
"How strictly are you
defining romance?"

01:39.316 --> 01:41.362
You may not make a movie
about the romance

01:41.405 --> 01:42.711
between a killer
and their weapon.

01:44.800 --> 01:47.237
Your film must make me
believe in love again.

01:47.281 --> 01:49.370
Anything less
will get an "F."

01:49.413 --> 01:50.545
You have one hour.

01:50.588 --> 01:53.243
Listen to me,
I sound just like Jamie.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.245
Take your time.

01:56.377 --> 01:57.334
Take your time.

01:57.378 --> 01:59.554
Maya: Hello,
prospective investors.

01:59.597 --> 02:01.947
We are two mums of
kids with disabilities,

02:01.991 --> 02:04.341
and we are starting a business
for people like us.

02:04.385 --> 02:06.256
Here's
a fascinating statistic

02:06.300 --> 02:07.736
about the adaptive-clothing
industry.

02:07.779 --> 02:08.954
Blah, blah, blah.

02:08.998 --> 02:09.825
Shocking, right?

02:09.868 --> 02:11.957
I had no idea.

02:12.001 --> 02:13.524
But what I do know is,

02:13.568 --> 02:15.352
insert completely improvised
yet heartfelt anecdote

02:15.396 --> 02:16.266
about parenting.

02:16.310 --> 02:18.834
But why tell you about
our amazing products

02:18.877 --> 02:19.791
when we can
just show you?

02:26.494 --> 02:28.800
Whoa!
I did not see that coming.

02:28.844 --> 02:30.019
And I loved it!

02:31.412 --> 02:33.370
It worked. It worked.Amazing, right?

02:33.414 --> 02:35.981
