at times,

12:36.233 --> 12:38.932
it will feel like a dog show.Hmm.

12:38.975 --> 12:40.324
Melanie: It's too bad.

12:40.368 --> 12:42.370
Kenneth was disappointed when
I told him I was leaving town.

12:42.413 --> 12:44.764
Oh, he knows our business
comes first.

12:44.807 --> 12:46.853
And you know,
regarding Kenneth,

12:46.896 --> 12:48.898
there are a few things
that you should know.

12:48.942 --> 12:50.204
He --

12:51.901 --> 12:53.337
Is right here.

12:54.208 --> 12:54.991
Hey, you.

12:58.081 --> 13:00.257
It feels like
we're playing Wembley!

13:00.301 --> 13:02.738
Soak it up, guys,
because tonight,

13:02.782 --> 13:05.741
for these kids, we are
the greatest band in the world.

13:05.785 --> 13:07.438
I want
to sing one.

13:07.482 --> 13:08.962
I'm tired of backing
you guys up.

13:09.005 --> 13:11.138
But you can't sing.And you can't
play guitar,

13:11.181 --> 13:12.443
but it doesn't
stop you.

13:12.487 --> 13:14.141
Easy, guys. Let's --
Let's just play.

13:14.184 --> 13:17.057
This is all
so small-minded.

13:17.100 --> 13:18.101
I'm out of here.
Come on, babe.

13:18.145 --> 13:19.668
Who is she?!

13:19.711 --> 13:21.365
Forget it.
Uh, "Free Fallin'."

13:21.409 --> 13:23.193
Ah, let's do
something fresher.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.499
"Wonderwall."Uh, new guy,

13:24.542 --> 13:25.848
that's not
really our sound.

13:25.892 --> 13:27.154
Well, "Free Fallin'"
isn't your sound either.

13:27.197 --> 13:28.808
You stole it
from John Mellencamp.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.812
No, no, don't look that up.
No, put your phones away.

13:32.855 --> 13:33.987
It's Tom Petty.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.640
Also, yeah, dude,
it's Tom Petty.

13:35.684 --> 13:36.641
You're a music exec?

13:38.078 --> 13:40.994
JJ, we are banging our heads
against a wall here, man.

13:41.037 --> 13:42.691
Izzy, you hungry?

13:42.734 --> 13:44.040
What do you say to some of
my famous braciole?

13:44.084 --> 13:46.651
No.
I love our banter.

13:46.695 --> 13:48.392
JJ, you should use this
in the script.

13:51.178 --> 13:54.137
"I'm going to get
some fresh air.

13:54.181 --> 13:55.008
You enjoy."

13:55.051 --> 13:58.098
I'm too tired
to stand.

13:58.141 --> 13:59.926
"Wow, sounds tough."

13:59.969 --> 14:02.145
Right.
That was terrible. Um...

14:02.189 --> 14:04.278
I shouldn't talk at all.

14:04.321 --> 14:06.976
Oh, God,
I made it worse.

14:07.020 --> 14:09.239
Uh, "Come on.
I have an idea."

14:11.067 --> 14:12.503
Izzy: Okay.

14:12.547 --> 14:15.855
"Maybe a car hits her,
and he saves her."

14:15.898 --> 14:17.900
No.
Why is this so hard?

14:17.944 --> 14:21.034
You seem to understand human
behavior in your other movies.

14:23.210 --> 14:25.560
"You saw my movies?"

14:25.603 --> 14:27.301
Yeah.

14:27.344 --> 14:28.432
They're great.

14:30.347 --> 14:33.263
"I'm suddenly very open
to your input."

14:33.307 --> 14:35.700
Well,
I don't know what to do.

14:35.744 --> 14:37.572
I'm no good at connecting
with people.

14:39.139 --> 14:40.401
I once had a lizard
I got close to.

14:42.316 --> 14:45.014
"Was he a football star
or a war hero?"

14:45.058 --> 14:47.060
No.

14:47.103 --> 14:49.540
Oh, you're being
charming.

14:49.584 --> 14:51.107
Write him like that.

14:51.151 --> 14:55.024
He should be real,
not perfect,

14:55.068 --> 14:59.115
someone who has a hard time
putting themselves out there

14:59.159 --> 15:01.030
but does it anyway.

15:01.074 --> 15:04.077
And he doesn't have
to save her life, you know.

15:04.120 --> 15:06.079
In these movies, it's more
about, like, a touch,

15:06.122 --> 15:09.082
and they feel
a connection.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.999
You write scary well.

15:13.042 --> 15:13.956
Pretend like
you're scared.

15:16.176 --> 15:18.526
How sweet.

15:18.569 --> 15:20.702
-Did you guys plan this?

15:21.790 --> 15:22.965
Uh, pretty much.

15:23.009 --> 15:25.185
Such a fun surprise.

15:25.228 --> 15:26.316
Ooh, let me go
freshen up.

15:28.884 --> 15:32.496
How dare you come here
and ruin our weekend.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.629
You only brought her here
to ruin myweekend.

15:34.672 --> 15:36.239
You just don't want me
to be happy.

15:36.283 --> 15:37.545
This is about
our business,

15:37.588 --> 15:40.461
and it cannot survive
with you interfering.

15:40.504 --> 15:42.506
She's gonna
have to choose.
Yeah.

15:42.550 --> 15:44.944
Yeah, either a lifetime
of ripping off pants

15:44.987 --> 15:47.250
or your dumb
adaptive-clothing line.

15:49.861 --> 15:52.125
Oh, you had to Tiffany
yourself up, didn't you?

15:52.168 --> 15:54.388
Melanie,
we need to talk,

15:54.431 --> 15:55.998
all of us.

15:56.042 --> 15:57.434
Are you two
breaking up with me?

15:57.478 --> 15:59.523
Don't be ridiculous.Oh, absolutely not.

15:59.567 --> 16:02.613
But we do need you
to break up with one of us.

16:05.094 --> 16:07.009
-Yeah.
-Wait, what?

16:07.053 --> 16:10.926
Melanie, we both
care about you so much,

16:10.970 --> 16:13.189
but sharing you
just isn't working out.

16:13.233 --> 16:16.062
So we need you
to pick one of us.

16:16.105 --> 16:18.107
-Me.
-Oh, please.

16:18.151 --> 16:21.197
Let the woman whose life
was in shambles before
she met me think.

16:21.241 --> 16:23.330
Wow. Look, I'm just getting
to know both of you.

16:23.373 --> 16:24.722
And now you want me
to pick one or the other?

16:27.812 --> 16:29.205
I'm sorry.
I choose neither.

16:32.600 --> 16:33.383
No, see, no,
you have to choose one.

16:37.344 --> 16:38.867
Sweetheart,

16:38.910 --> 16:41.087
I know you're mad.
It's just...

16:42.262 --> 16:45.787
Life's hard, and it felt good
to get some glory,

16:45.830 --> 16:47.484
just for
one brief moment.

16:47.528 --> 16:49.965
I'm sorry.
Can you forgive me?

16:50.009 --> 16:52.402
Do you have anything
to say for yourself?

16:52.446 --> 16:56.232
Well, I think
what happened is,

16:56.276 --> 16:59.061
you thought we wrote
"Satisfaction,"

16:59.105 --> 17:02.238
so I lied
and said I did.

17:02.282 --> 17:04.284
And that felt great.

17:04.327 --> 17:05.372
And then a bunch
of your friends

17:05.415 --> 17:06.764
thought we wrote
"Satisfaction."

17:06.808 --> 17:08.114
Then we got caught,

17:08.157 --> 17:10.899
and then
I bought chocolate milk,

17:10.942 --> 17:11.943
and now we're here,
yeah.

17:13.336 --> 17:15.425
-So no takeaway?

17:15.469 --> 17:17.210
Not really, no.

17:17.253 --> 17:19.038
No, I think
I'm just an idiot.

17:19.081 --> 17:22.345
Well, I guess you could say
that we lived dangerously,

17:22.389 --> 17:23.477
we paid the price,

17:23.520 --> 17:25.914
and we -- we survived
to tell the tale.

17:25.957 --> 17:30.266
And that is what
rock 'n' roll is all about.

17:30.310 --> 17:31.876
Now, see, that feels
like a takeaway.

17:31.920 --> 17:34.792
I learned nothing,
and I would do it again.

17:34.836 --> 17:37.360
In fact, do you have any friends
who weren't here tonight

17:37.404 --> 17:39.145
but also don't know
a lot about music?

17:39.188 --> 17:41.234
The track team?The track team.

17:41.277 --> 17:42.583
Right in front of me
all this time.

17:42.626 --> 17:44.367
Come on.

17:44.411 --> 17:46.108
Why can't you be
more like her?

17:46.152 --> 17:48.545
And she chose neither of us.
It's over.

17:48.589 --> 17:50.199
You didn't even
fight for her?

17:50.243 --> 17:53.420
As the lead
in a romantic comedy,

17:53.463 --> 17:57.337
I know you cannot
take no for an answer.

17:57.380 --> 17:59.600
"Actually, Izzy pointed out
that trope

17:59.643 --> 18:01.471
has a really toxic
message."

18:01.515 --> 18:03.517
"Don't take no
for an answer."

18:03.560 --> 18:05.084
I like it.

18:05.127 --> 18:06.259
Yeah. Impress her.

18:06.302 --> 18:08.130
Win a karate tournament.

18:08.174 --> 18:09.175
Become a billionaire

18:09.218 --> 18:11.351
and save the dumb dock
where her dad works.

18:11.394 --> 18:12.917
What was I thinking?

18:12.961 --> 18:15.094
Melanie and I
are meant to be together.

18:15.137 --> 18:18.053
I'm gonna stop talking
to my diverse sidekicks

18:18.097 --> 18:19.359
and go
and get the girl.

18:22.666 --> 18:23.624
Where are you going?

18:23.667 --> 18:26.279
To get more
mango juice.

18:26.322 --> 18:28.281
Good luck getting
Melanie back, Mom!

18:28.324 --> 18:30.196
You're blocking me in!

18:30.239 --> 18:32.154
Then I guess
I'll get there first!

18:35.810 --> 18:37.203
Maya, get out.

18:37.246 --> 18:38.204
I'm winning her back,

18:38.247 --> 18:39.683
and I'm not taking no
for an answer.

18:39.727 --> 18:43.339
Do you have any idea
how toxic that trope is?

18:44.340 --> 18:47.691
We need to talk.Shh! It's the library.

18:47.735 --> 18:49.345
I've been quiet
long enough.

18:49.389 --> 18:51.260
I didn't
go looking for this,

18:51.304 --> 18:53.393
but I felt something
last night.

18:54.611 --> 18:56.526
Don't listen to him.
He's just going to hurt you.

18:56.570 --> 18:57.440
Shh!

18:57.484 --> 19:00.095
I have to work so hard

19:00.139 --> 19:01.444
to be understood,

19:01.488 --> 19:02.880
but you just saw me.

19:02.924 --> 19:05.056
It was scary.
Izzy: Oh.

19:05.100 --> 19:07.450
Should I
leave you alone?

19:07.494 --> 19:09.409
That scares me
even more.

19:12.151 --> 19:13.500
Wow.
That was really good.

19:13.543 --> 19:16.067
Um, should I
kiss him?

19:19.201 --> 19:21.508
Where did you
find this girl? Yes!

19:21.551 --> 19:24.163
Kenneth, I understand
why you're upset.

19:24.206 --> 19:25.686
I mean,
I know you like Melanie.

19:25.729 --> 19:27.557
But you have
to understand --

19:27.601 --> 19:29.951
with JJ going away
to college next year --

19:29.994 --> 19:31.909
Maya, this isn't
about you.

19:31.953 --> 19:34.999
Are you sure?
Feels like it is.

19:35.043 --> 19:36.610
You know why you've never
seen me in a relationship?

19:36.653 --> 19:38.960
Because ever since
I met you,

19:39.003 --> 19:42.268
my whole life has been
about you and your family.

19:42.311 --> 19:44.357
But who cares.

19:44.400 --> 19:48.274
In Maya-land, nothing exists
outside of the DiMeos.

19:48.317 --> 19:50.493
Well, I get
to have something, too.

19:50.537 --> 19:53.540
Oh, Kenneth, I can really
see how you feel.

19:55.759 --> 19:57.326
Maya!

19:58.893 --> 20:01.765
Come on!
I gave you a ride, lady!

20:01.809 --> 20:04.028
Let me have this!

20:05.421 --> 20:07.510
What are you
doing here?
Melanie,

20:07.554 --> 20:09.425
you are
an amazing woman,

20:09.469 --> 20:12.254
and you deserve to have
an equally amazing partner.

20:12.298 --> 20:14.300
Now, maybe we can
work this out

20:14.343 --> 20:16.650
where you don't have to choose
between me or Kenneth.

20:16.693 --> 20:18.739
But if you have
to choose...

20:18.782 --> 20:21.394
Can you hear my voice
at this level?

20:21.437 --> 20:22.960
Choose Kenneth.

20:23.004 --> 20:24.310
Really?
But you're still mad at him.

20:24.353 --> 20:26.355
Well, I mean,
things got weird.

20:26.399 --> 20:27.748
But, you know,

20:27.791 --> 20:31.142
I like how he dresses like
it's summer all year round.

20:31.186 --> 20:33.101
And I love
how he sings

20:33.144 --> 20:35.321
what he needs to tell you
when he could...

20:35.364 --> 20:38.411
♪ Just bloody say it

20:40.500 --> 20:43.416
But, I mean, what I like best
about him is that he's kind

20:43.459 --> 20:45.505
and he's fantastic
with my son

20:45.548 --> 20:48.899
and he has a very,
very big heart.

20:48.943 --> 20:50.684
And he really likes you,
Melanie.

20:50.727 --> 20:53.513
Well, shouldn't he
be telling me all this?

20:53.556 --> 20:54.557
I'm the one
sacrificing you,

20:54.601 --> 20:56.080
so I didn't want him
coming in here

20:56.124 --> 20:57.386
and messing it all up.

20:57.430 --> 20:59.432
Plus,
I wanted the big moment.

20:59.475 --> 21:02.086
Please forgive him,

21:02.130 --> 21:04.393
and I promise
I won't interfere anymore.

21:09.398 --> 21:10.356
Hey, you.

21:10.399 --> 21:12.358
Oh, God, you heard.

21:12.401 --> 21:17.450
♪ You're so special
to me ♪

21:18.494 --> 21:20.757
Oh. Oh, right.

21:23.456 --> 21:24.326
Ew.
